        <h2>Comcast Cable v. Sprint</h2>
        <p><strong>Case #38</strong> | Expert Witness: Dr. Tal Lavian</p>

<p>This matter involves Comcast Cable as the petitioner and Sprint as the patent owner. Dr. Tal Lavian was retained as an expert witness to provide technical analysis and testimony on issues related to telecommunications, network communications, and internet protocol technologies.</p>
        <h3>Expert Witness Qualifications</h3>
        <p>Dr. Lavian brings over 25 years of experience in telecommunications and network communications. His expertise includes network architecture, internet protocols, VoIP systems, mobile and wireless communications, interactive voice response (IVR) systems, frequency synthesis, and autonomous vehicle sensing technologies.</p>
        <p>Dr. Lavian holds a Ph.D. from UC Berkeley and has authored over 80 patents in telecommunications and network communications. His expert testimony is grounded in both academic research and extensive industry experience at companies including Nortel Networks, AT&amp;T, and Juniper Networks.</p>
        <h3>Expert Services Provided</h3>
        <p>In this matter, Dr. Lavian's expert services may have included one or more of the following: claim construction analysis, invalidity and validity opinions, infringement analysis, technical tutorials for counsel and the court, deposition testimony, trial testimony, and preparation of expert reports.</p>

        <p>For a complete list of cases where Dr. Lavian has provided expert witness services, please visit the <a href="/cases-expert-witness-testimony/">Cases</a> page.</p>

